  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220°C/ 200°C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil half a kettle</p><p>Put a large baking tray (or two!) in the oven to heat up (this will stop the base of your naan from going soggy!)</p><p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>shallot[s]</strong>, then combine the <strong>sliced shallot </strong>with your<strong> red wine vinegar</strong>, 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> in a small bowl and set aside – this is your <strong>quick-pickled shallot</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-1-1610968449392-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
